Deferred Entry of Judgment Agreement

Court calls Case No. 16CF1 and 16CF63.  Defendant Brianne M. Klabunde in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement placed on the record by Atty Tlusty.  16CF1 - DE enters a plea of no contest to Cts. 1-3.  16CF63 - DE enters a plea of no contest to Ct. 1.  Factual basis exists.  Court finds plea given freely, voluntarily and intelligently; accepts plea; finds DE guilty.  16CF1 - Court withheld sentence and placed DE on probation for 2 years for Cts. 1 & 3 with additional conditions of: court costs; 10 days county jail, but stayed for rules violations; DNA sample and surcharge; AODA; random drug testing; counseling as deemed appropriate by agent; authorized  transfer of probation to MN. Ct. 2 - Pursuant to the agreement the court deferred entry of Judgment of Conviction for a period of two years and signed same. 16CF63 - Court imposed on Ct. 1 - Court costs; DNA sample and surcharge.  Cts. 2 & 3 are dismissed, but read in.
